menu "Board Common"

    config BOARD_LANDSCAPE
        bool "Landscape orientation"
        default n
        help
            Rotate the display 90 degrees for landscape orientation.

            When enabled, LVGL sees swapped dimensions (V_RES x H_RES)
            and the board init code applies the appropriate flush callback
            rotation and touch coordinate transforms.

            The convenience macros BOARD_DISP_H_RES / BOARD_DISP_V_RES
            reflect the logical (post-rotation) dimensions.

    config BOARD_CSI_AE_TARGET
        int "CSI camera auto-exposure target (0 = ISP default)"
        default 0
        range 0 235
        help
            Auto-exposure setpoint for the CSI (OV5647) ISP pipeline, 2-235.
            Higher = brighter; 128 = neutral. 0 leaves the ISP/sensor default,
            which over-exposes when scanning bright backlit screens (QR module
            highlights clip). Set ~60-80 to dial exposure back for on-screen QR
            scanning without dimming the source. Applied at camera start.

endmenu
